The paper deals with learning algorithms and compression schemes, which are typically studied in the machine learning and data structures subfields of computer science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves the concept of VC dimension, which is a measure of the complexity of a class of functions, and is often used in computational complexity theory and information theory. Hence, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper uses an approximate minimax phenomenon for binary matrices, which is a concept from game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category.
